cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.CYBER, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the recent trends towards digitalization and large scale data analytics in healthcare, which involves the use of technology and data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), which focuses on the design, evaluation, and implementation of interactive computing systems for human use. 

The paper also discusses the use of networks of healthcare providers, research organizations, and commercial vendors to jointly analyze data, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). 

The trend towards continuous healthcare and the use of wearable and stationary devices for health monitoring is related to the field of cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity), as it involves the protection of sensitive health data. 

The paper also mentions cost pressure as a major driver of innovation, which could fall under the category of cs.CE (Computational Economics) as it involves the use of computational methods to study economic systems. 

Finally, the paper discusses the trend towards personalized medicine, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it involves the protection of sensitive health data through encryption and other security measures.
